items.name: POV Handjob
items.description:
It's a LoRA that I decided to train after remembering those dating sim games where they show CGI of the character and you had to click on their penis to stimulate them. Luckily, this LoRA would feature a stimulating hand.

I'm still learning how to properly build and train LoRAs, so don't expect it to be flawless. This LoRA's goal is to incorporate a low angle view of a character with exposed penis and the viewer's hand stroking it. Because the AI has difficulty with fingers, the training footage typically comprise the visible thumb with the rest of the fingers covered behind the shaft. As with any hand POV LoRA, expect it to function 80% of the time, depending on the art style of your model. If a hand doesn't spawn, you can increase the LoRA strength or simply enjoy a handless handjob from a low angle. If the hand is glitching or the fingers are mutated, you can use Img2Img or Inpaint.

Side effects: two or more hands can spawn; extremely long penis; most characters are smiling for some reason

items.name: Umi Kousaka/高坂海美 | MILLION LIVE!/ミリオンライブ/ミリシタ
items.description:
LoRA model of Umi Kousaka (高坂海美) from media-mix project THE IDOLM@STER MILLION LIVE! (アイドルマスターミリオンライブ！).

The trigger word is umi kousaka (million live). Considering the Second Hair Style (SHS) card in Mirishita, this model don't fix Umi's hairstyle. You can reproduce the Umi's style of game card illustrations by adding following tags:

*Original hairstyle of Umi:

twin braids, long hair

*Second Hair Style of Umi:

 high ponytail, side ponytail, long hair

Of course, you can change features of hairstyle at your own. Try and enjoy it!

The LoRA weight of samples is 0.8-0.85; you can also try other weights. The greater the weight, the closer the character style is to the game card of THE IDOLM@STER MILLION LIVE! THEATER DAYS (ミリシタ) and the new tachie drawn after the release of the game.

Note: I load my LoRA model through the additional network WebUI plugin, so the prompt of sample illustrations don't contain <lora:XXX:X> tag.

I'll appreciate it if you're willing to use this LoRA model and share AI arts to other people. My models and illustrations are free for everyone, and if you like them, please support me at Patreon or 爱发电.

items.name: Giants and Shrinks Concept LoHa (SDXL)
items.description:
• Current version: v1.0

  • Recommended weight: 0.8-1.0 (the more LoRa's are chained together the lower this needs to be)

  • Recommended VAE: SDXL 0.9

  • Recommended model: SDXL 1.0

  • Recommended inference settings: See example images

I recommend using the official SDXL 1.0 model that has the SDXL 0.9 VAE already integrated, which you can find here.

Trigger words

  • giant x

  • miniature x

  • giant x cramped inside a room

Further usage notes

Prompting just "giant woman" or "miniature woman" will not prompt the size. You need to tie it to an action/position like "giant woman standing in a city street" or "miniature woman standing on a forest ground next to a mushroom"!

This LoHa tends to generate naked women if you do not negative prompt "naked" and/or specifically mention clothing in the positive prompt.

This LoHa works best when using a render style in the positive prompt, while photos and digital art work less well.

This LoHa was generally trained on three distinct concepts: giant people in a city, giant people cramped inside rooms, and miniature people. It thus works best with those concepts and with people, but you may try other concepts and subjects, too.

Use "toy, figurine" in the negative prompt to prevent the subject from becoming an action figure when prompting miniature people.

Changelog

v1.0

  • Initial release

Description

Giants and Shrinks Concept LoHa for SDXL 1.0 trained (not merged) by me (AI_Characters). Credit is not mandatory but I would still appreciate credit when posting images using this LoHa on social media! Feel free to @ my Twitter and/or Instagram accounts too (@ai_characters)! I would love to know when it is used!

If you want to support what I am doing, donations to my Ko-Fi would be greatly appreciated! Those will go towards funding the renting of GPUs for further experimentation and model making.

Feel free to also try out my RVC2 AI voice models which you can find here!

Stats

Dataset:

  • 94 images (renders and artworks)

Training:

  • rented RTX A4090 on Vast.ai

  • Training time: ~1h

  • Example training configuration (v3)

items.name: KevaMix
items.description:
V3 Instruction

Here's a new version of this model. I found that the model I had updated, V2, was veering a bit too far from the style I intended to showcase with this model. Therefore, I reworked this model and achieved a satisfactory result.

Here are the recommended settings:

Sample: DPM++ 2M Karras

Steps: 30-40 (going below 30 to 20 is feasible, but I personally found that the images looked better between 30 and 40)

VAE: vae-ft-ema-560000-ema-pruned.ckpt (this is the one I used, but experimenting with another one might potentially yield improved results)

Upscaler: 4x-Ultrasharp, as it allows for preserving the desired style in the images. R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B could work, but I feel it slightly deviates from the intended style, though it still remains good overall. It will depend on your preferences.

INTRODUCTION

I created this model by merging a model that I had already been created that I had a while ago but never shared since it didn't have anything special by combining several existing Anime models . So, I merged my Lora with this model called Nier Character Style, and I found the images generated by this model interesting and quite different from what I've seen before. Perhaps this model resembles other models, but it was not my intention to plagiarize anyone.

INSTRUCTIONS:

Let me explain how to use this model; I apologize if I omit some information as I am a beginner in model creation.

This model allows you to generate anime images based on the style of the Nier series illustrations. I created this model out of curiosity to see the result of merging a model with a Lora. I was happy with the result, so I decided to share it with you.

I made this model just for fun, and I hope you will enjoy it!

I tested this model with different parameters:

I used this model with the following VAEs:

  • vae-ft-ema-560000-ema-pruned

  • kl-f8-anime2

I didn't notice any significant differences in the results.

I also tried using the following samplers:

  • Euler a

  • DPM++ 2M Karras

  • DPM++ SDE Karras

All of these samplers can give you satisfying results; I didn't observe one sampler being superior to the others. Personally, I use the DPM++ 2M Karras sampler for all my image generations.

I recommend using the ADetailer extension to save time and achieve more successful facial results.

As for upscaling, you can use the R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B model.

Since I merged my Lora, you may use the keyword 'nier_artstyle' if you find it enhances the results, but it is not mandatory

Regarding the steps, I would recommend setting it between 30 and 40. However, you can still achieve satisfactory results below this range:

WIP MODEL

Aims to remedy the issue in some detail sliders where the "detail" increase ends up effecting the overall composition of the image. Results are similar to Add More Details as the model uses it as a base, which I highly recommend using.

Versions:

  • Main: The base one

  • Alt: Slightly better results IMO but 300mb because I hate having room on my harddrive and 256 dim sounded fun

  • Alt2: Less lighting weight, probably better but 🤷‍♀️

Current issues:

  • Still noticeable impact on characters, namely their ethnicity/skin color.

  • Neither have clip/text encoding training, this isn't really an issue though IMO

I'm working on a better version that should produce better results overall, but for now this is good enough. I might also release a few that target specific areas instead of producing more defined/sharp results, like one for realism

items.name: Pokémon movies and specials - Style | LoRA
items.description:
This is a style cocreated with @Yoshi_ (dataset and testing), made with a bunch of images from the first five Pokémon movies and some specials which are truer to Ken Sugimori original designs.

I have a kofi if you want to support my work. I also take commissions, so if you are interested on a training, check that out. I also have a Pixiv where I upload pics from testing and tease the things I'm working on! Or go to my wife's Pixiv, she has sexy pics of my LoRAs and WIPs.

items.description:
There are several kinds of Oyster Omelet in Southeast parts of China.

在中国东南部有多种海蛎煎饼。

The Lora is about the Zhangzhou Urban Style. Dataset used the Zhangzhou Urban Style.

这一Lora是关于漳州市区风格的海蛎煎饼。数据集使用的是漳州市区风格。

Hokkien/South Fujian People called it 蚝（蚵）仔煎O-a-zian(Zhangzhou local pronunciation) in dialect and 海蛎煎（饼）Haili jian(bing) in mandarin, while Teochow/Chaozhou-Shantou People call it 蚝烙O-luah.

闽南人方言称之蚝/蚵仔煎，用普通话则是海蛎煎（饼），潮州人则是称之蚝烙。

It said that People in the urban of Zhangzhou prefer to use rice flour, though usually sweet potato starch was used, according to one of my schoolmates, who lived in the urban of Zhangzhou. I lived with My grandfather in suburb, who is a Sichuanese Hakka. He used flour with sweet potato starch.

据我一为漳州市区的同学称，市区人偏好使用米粉，虽然通常用地瓜粉（番薯淀粉/红苕淀粉）。我和我外公住在郊区，他是四川客家人。他用的是面粉加地瓜粉。

items.description:

How to Use This Model

USE THEM SIMULTANEOUSLY. In this case, you need to download both myrtle_arknights.pt and myrtle_arknights.safetensors, then use myrtle_arknights.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use myrtle_arknights.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

それらを同時に使用してください。この場合、myrtle_arknights.ptとmyrtle_arknights.safetensorsの両方をダウンロード する必要があります。myrtle_arknights.ptをテクスチャ反転埋め込みとして使用し、同時にmyrtle_arknights.safetensorsをLoRAとして使用してください。

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Myrtle Arknights

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is fine-tune the tags you use.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/myrtle_arknights, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/myrtle_arknights, which may be help to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

Taiwanese braised pork rice is a popular Taiwanese dish made with rice, braised pork, and a variety of toppings. The braised pork is typically made with pork belly, which is slow-cooked in a soy sauce, sugar, and spice mixture until it is tender and flavorful. The rice is then cooked in the same pot with the braised pork, absorbing the flavors of the sauce. The dish is then topped with a variety of ingredients, such as pickled vegetables, scallions, and cilantro.

Taiwanese braised pork rice is a delicious and hearty dish that is perfect for a quick meal or a leisurely lunch. It is also a great source of protein and carbohydrates, making it a good choice for people who are active or who are trying to gain weight.

Here are some tips for making the best Taiwanese braised pork rice:

  • Use high-quality pork belly. High-quality pork belly will have a good amount of fat, which will help to keep the meat moist and flavorful.

  • Use a good quality soy sauce. A good quality soy sauce will add depth and complexity to the flavor of the dish.

  • Don't overcook the pork. Overcooked pork will be tough and dry.

  • Use a variety of toppings. The toppings you choose will add different flavors and textures to the dish.

Taiwanese braised pork rice is a delicious and versatile dish that can be enjoyed by people of all ages. It is easy to make and can be customized to your liking. So next time you are looking for a quick and easy meal, be sure to try Taiwanese braised pork rice!
